The paper discusses the recent advances in artificial intelligence (AI) and the need to push AI to the network edge to fully utilize the potential of edge big data. It specifically focuses on the emerging paradigm of edge computing and its intersection with AI, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
